    "The one with the larger $x$-coordinate is $(10, 3)$.",
    "The answer is: $\\boxed{(10, 3)}$.",
    "The given equation is of an ellipse in the standard form \\[\\frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2} + \\frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2} = 1,\\] where \\((h, k)\\) is the center of the ellipse, \\(a\\) is the semi-major axis length, and \\(b\\) is the semi-minor axis length.",
